In this statement, President Obama acknowledges the upcoming National Day of Thanksgiving and emphasizes the importance of remembering the origins of the holiday, which involved European settlers and Native Americans coming together for a harvest celebration. He encourages Americans to observe Native American Heritage Day as a way to honor and appreciate the rich culture, traditions, and history of Native Americans. The President also expresses his commitment to strengthening the relationship between tribal governments and the nation as a whole, while recognizing the contributions that Native Americans have made and will continue to make to the United States.